# Backend

This is the server-side of the Blog Ninja application. It is responsible for handling CRUD operations for blog posts.

## Tech Stack

The backend is written in Express.js.

## Setup

To set up the backend locally, follow these steps:

1. Navigate to the `back-end` directory.
2. Install the dependencies using `npm install`.
3. Start the server using `npm start`.

## API Endpoints

The backend provides the following API endpoints:

- `GET /posts`: Fetch all blog posts.
- `POST /posts`: Create a new blog post.
- `GET /posts/:id`: Fetch a specific blog post.
- `PUT /posts/:id`: Update a specific blog post.
- `DELETE /posts/:id`: Delete a specific blog post.
